The paper deals with the problem of estimating human pose from images, which is a common task in computer vision. The use of Deep Convolutional Neural Networks (DCNNs) to learn conditional probabilities for the presence of parts and their spatial relationships within image patches suggests that the paper belongs to the Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the use of graphical models and mixture models suggests that the paper may also belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The use of image measurements and spatial relationships also suggests that the paper may belong to the Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the problem of estimating human pose from images is also relevant to Robotics (cs.RO), which suggests that this sub-category is also a likely fit for this paper.
